  "local_port": 34120,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What do I eat on the Ketogenics Diet?",
  "response": "The **Ketogenic (Keto) Diet** is a low-carbohydrate, high-fat eating plan designed to shift your body\u2019s metabolism from burning carbohydrates for energy to burning fat, a state known as ketosis. When following a ketogenic diet, it's essential to focus on high-fat, moderate-protein, and very low-carbohydrate foods. Here's a comprehensive guide on what to eat and what to avoid:\n\n### **Foods to Eat**\n\n1. **Meats and Poultry**\n   - **Beef, Pork, Lamb:** Opt for fattier cuts to increase fat intake.\n   - **Poultry:** Chicken, turkey, and duck with skin.\n\n2. **Fatty Fish and Seafood**\n   - **Salmon, Trout, Mackerel, Sardines:** Rich in omega-3 fatty acids.\n   - **Shellfish:** Shrimp, crab, and lobster in moderation.\n\n3. **Eggs**\n   - **Whole Eggs:** A versatile and nutrient-dense option.\n\n4. **Dairy Products**\n   - **Cheese:** Cheddar, mozzarella, cream cheese.\n   - **Butter and Cream:** Use in cooking or as additions to meals.\n   - **Full-Fat Yogurt and Greek Yogurt:** In moderation, without added sugars.\n\n5. **Healthy Fats and Oils**\n   - **Olive Oil, Coconut Oil, Avocado Oil:** For cooking and dressing salads.\n   - **Lard and Tallow:** Traditional cooking fats.\n\n6. **Low-Carb Vegetables**\n   - **Leafy Greens:** Spinach, kale, arugula.\n   - **Cruciferous Vegetables:** Broccoli, cauliflower, Brussels sprouts.\n   - **Others:** Zucchini, bell peppers, asparagus.\n\n7. **Nuts and Seeds**\n   - **Almonds, Walnuts, Pecans, Macadamia Nuts:** In moderation due to carb content.\n   - **Chia Seeds, Flaxseeds, Pumpkin Seeds:** Great for adding texture and nutrients.\n\n8. **Avocados**\n   - Rich in healthy fats and fiber.\n\n9. **Berries**\n   - **Strawberries, Raspberries, Blackberries:** Limited quantities due to lower carb content.\n\n10. **Beverages**\n    - **Water:** Aim for plenty of hydration.\n    - **Coffee and Tea:** Without added sugars; you can add cream or unsweetened almond milk.\n\n### **Foods to Avoid**\n\n1. **Sugary Foods and Beverages**\n   - **Sodas, Fruit Juices, Candies, Cakes, and Ice Creams.**\n\n2. **Grains and Starches**\n   - **Bread, Pasta, Rice, Cereals, and Tortillas.**\n\n3. **High-Carb Fruits**\n   - **Bananas, Apples, Oranges, Grapes, and Mangoes.**\n\n4. **Starchy Vegetables**\n   - **Potatoes, Sweet Potatoes, Corn, and Peas.**\n\n5. **Legumes**\n   - **Beans, Lentils, Chickpeas, and Peas.**\n\n6. **Unhealthy Fats**\n   - **Processed Vegetable Oils (e.g., Canola, Soy), Margarine, and Trans Fats.**\n\n7. **Alcoholic Beverages**\n   - **Beer, Sweet Wines, and Cocktails:** Generally high in carbs.\n   - **Dry Wines and Spirits:** In moderation, as some contain fewer carbs.\n\n8. **Processed and Packaged Foods**\n   - Often contain hidden sugars and unhealthy fats.\n\n### **Sample Meal Ideas**\n\n- **Breakfast:** Scrambled eggs cooked in butter with spinach and avocado slices.\n- **Lunch:** Grilled chicken salad with mixed greens, olive oil dressing, feta cheese, and olives.\n- **Dinner:** Baked salmon with a side of roasted broccoli and cauliflower, drizzled with garlic butter.\n- **Snacks:** A handful of walnuts, cheese slices, or cucumber slices with cream cheese.\n\n### **Tips for Success**\n\n- **Track Your Macros:** Maintain a balance of approximately 70-75% fat, 20-25% protein, and 5-10% carbohydrates.\n- **Stay Hydrated:** Drink plenty of water and consider electrolyte supplementation.\n- **Plan Meals Ahead:** Helps in maintaining the diet and avoiding high-carb temptations.\n- **Listen to Your Body:** Adjust the diet based on how you feel and your individual health needs.\n\n### **Caution**\n\nBefore starting any new diet, including the ketogenic diet, it's advisable to consult with a healthcare professional or a registered dietitian, especially if you have underlying health conditions or are taking medications. They can provide personalized guidance and ensure that the diet aligns with your health goals.",
